<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="J" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Juggle" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Juggle,</orth> vb. to play tricks, to practise imposture: <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.169" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.68" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 4, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 3, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.8.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 8, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.5.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 5, 130</bibl>. With an accus. denoting the effect: <cit><quote>the spells of France should j. men into such strange mysteries,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 3, 1</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>